            <title>[OAK-2670] Online Backup of segment store fails on Windows because the journal file is locked exclusively.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2670</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The SegmentStore implementation org.apache.jackrabbit.oak.plugins.segment.file.FileStore uses an exclusive lock on the journal file to prevent a repository from restarting that hasn&apos;t been shutdown properly (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1696&quot; title=&quot;Repository  fails to restart on Windows&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-1696&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-1696&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). Therefore the journal file can&apos;t be copied when the repo is online.&lt;br/&gt;
Solution proposal: using a dedicated file for locking should suffice.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
